      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Sanjoy Mahajan</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:182px;\"><a href=\"http://streetfightingmath.com/author.html\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/5/5d/Mahajan_sanjoy.jpg\" width=\"180\" height=\"241\" class=\"thumbimage\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Mahajan_sanjoy.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Sanjoy Mahajan <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Sanjoy Mahajan</b>, <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><br />\na British American physicist, mathematician, electrical engineer and computer scientist <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>. He is associate professor of applied science and engineering at <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Franklin_W._Olin_College_of_Engineering\">Franklin W. Olin College of Engineering</a> and visiting associate professor of electrical engineering and computer science at <a href=\"/Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology\" title=\"Massachusetts Institute of Technology\">Massachusetts Institute of Technology</a>. \nBefore, he was a physics lecturer at the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_Cambridge\">University of Cambridge</a>, with interests in improving physics and mathematics teaching and in writing textbooks, supported by the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gatsby_Charitable_Foundation\">Gatsby Charitable Trust</a>. \nSanjoy Mahajan holds a B.Sc. in physics from <a href=\"/Stanford_University\" title=\"Stanford University\">Stanford University</a> in 1990, and a Ph.D. in physics in 1998 from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/California_Institute_of_Technology\">California Institute of Technology</a>, where his advisors were <a href=\"/Mathematician#SPhinney\" title=\"Mathematician\">Sterl Phinney</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#JHopfield\" title=\"Mathematician\">John Hopfield</a> and <a href=\"/Mathematician#CAMead\" title=\"Mathematician\">Carver Mead</a>. The thesis included <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biophysics\">theoretical biophysics</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probabilistic_number_theory\">probabilistic number theory</a>, and a draft textbook on order-of-magnitude physics <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>. \nHe is author of <i>Street-Fighting Mathematics</i> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> and <i>The Art of Insight in Science and Engineering</i> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Bill\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Bill</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Selected_Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#1986_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1986 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#1990_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">1990 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2000_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2000 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Bill\">Bill</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sanjoy_Mahajan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Bill\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>During the mid and late 80s, along with <a href=\"/Kai-Fu_Lee\" title=\"Kai-Fu Lee\">Kai-Fu Lee</a>, Sanjoy Mahajan co-authored the at that time world class <a href=\"/Othello\" title=\"Othello\">Othello</a> program <i>Bill</i> <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>, \ninitially written in <a href=\"/index.php?title=LISP&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"LISP (page does not exist)\">Common Lisp</a> at <a href=\"/Carnegie_Mellon_University\" title=\"Carnegie Mellon University\">Carnegie Mellon University</a> in 1985, in 1986 rewritten in <a href=\"/C\" title=\"C\">C</a> and in 2005 released under the <a href=\"/Free_Software_Foundation#GPL\" title=\"Free Software Foundation\">GPL</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>. \n<i>Bill 3.0</i> applied <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bayesian_inference\">Bayesian learning</a> of <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discriminant_function_analysis\">discriminant functions</a> that <a href=\"/Automated_Tuning\" title=\"Automated Tuning\">automatically combines</a> <a href=\"/Evaluation\" title=\"Evaluation\">evaluation</a> features <sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>  <sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_Publications\">Selected Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sanjoy_Mahajan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Selected Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> <sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1986_...\">1986 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sanjoy_Mahajan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: 1986 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Kai-Fu_Lee\" title=\"Kai-Fu Lee\">Kai-Fu Lee</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://kilthub.cmu.edu/articles/BILL_a_table-based_knowledge-intensive_othello_program/6603887/1\">BILL: a table-based, knowledge-intensive othello program</a></i>. Technial Report CMU-CS-86-141, <a href=\"/Carnegie_Mellon_University\" title=\"Carnegie Mellon University\">Carnegie Mellon University</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://pdfs.semanticscholar.org/f7ab/15736ecc79452aa4546cf8d7f5aa94d6afa0.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Kai-Fu_Lee\" title=\"Kai-Fu Lee\">Kai-Fu Lee</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>1988</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/0004370288900768\">A Pattern Classification Approach to Evaluation Function Learning</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_Intelligence_%28journal%29\">Artificial Intelligence</a>, Vol. 36, No. 1</li>\n<li> <a href=\"/Kai-Fu_Lee\" title=\"Kai-Fu Lee\">Kai-Fu Lee</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>1989</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Corrective-and-reinforcement-learning-for-speech-Lee-Mahajan/ea82f514e0e00586f00402a4df2cd0885b4e13c5\">Corrective and Reinforcement Learning for Speaker-independent continuous Speech Recognition</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://dblp.uni-trier.de/db/conf/interspeech/eurospeech1989.html\">EUROSPEECH 1989</a> </li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"1990_...\">1990 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sanjoy_Mahajan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 1990 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a href=\"/Kai-Fu_Lee\" title=\"Kai-Fu Lee\">Kai-Fu Lee</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>1990</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/000437029090068B\">The Development of a World Class Othello Program</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artificial_Intelligence_%28journal%29\">Artificial Intelligence</a>, Vol. 43, No. 1</li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>1998</b>). <i>Order of Magnitude Physics - A Textbook with Applications to the Retinal Rod and to the Density of Prime Numbers</i>. Ph.D. thesis, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/California_Institute_of_Technology\">California Institute of Technology</a>, advisors <a href=\"/Mathematician#SPhinney\" title=\"Mathematician\">Sterl Phinney</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#JHopfield\" title=\"Mathematician\">John Hopfield</a> and <a href=\"/Mathematician#CAMead\" title=\"Mathematician\">Carver Mead</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.inference.phy.cam.ac.uk/sanjoy/thesis/thesis-letter.pdf\">pdf</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2000_...\">2000 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sanjoy_Mahajan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2000 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>2001</b>). <i>A Radical Experiment in Mathematics Teaching</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.inference.phy.cam.ac.uk/sanjoy/ihpst/benezet.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>2001</b>). <i>Physics students learn nothing, so try history of science</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.inference.phy.cam.ac.uk/sanjoy/ihpst/rote-physics.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>2001</b>). <i>Learning proof and questioning lies</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.inference.phy.cam.ac.uk/sanjoy/ihpst/proof.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>2002</b>). <i>Estimating light bending using order-of-magnitude physics</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.inference.phy.cam.ac.uk/sanjoy/teaching/approximation/light-bending.pdf\">pdf</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Physics Education Research: Or it’s so hard to find good help these days</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://arxiv.org/abs/physics/0405006\">arXiv:physics/0405006</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://as.nyu.edu/content/nyu-as/as/faculty/david-w-hogg.html\">David W. Hogg</a> (<b>2004</b>). <i>Introductory physics: The new scholasticism</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/physics/0412107\">arXiv:physics/0412107</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=10EI2q8AAAAJ&amp;hl=en\">Richard R. Hake</a> (<b>2005</b>). <i>Is it finally time for a physics counterpart of the Benezet–Berman math experiment of the 1930’s?</i> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/physics/0512202v1\">arXiv:physics/0512202v1</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>2005</b>). <i>Estimating gas mileage: An example of order-of-magnitude physics</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/physics/0512209\">arXiv:physics/0512209</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>2007</b>). <i>Teaching for transfer</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/0704.1854\">arXiv:0704.1854</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sanjoy_Mahajan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>2010</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://mitpress.mit.edu/books/street-fighting-mathematics\">Street-Fighting Mathematics: The Art of Educated Guessing and Opportunistic Problem Solving</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIT_Press\">MIT Press</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>2012</b>). <i>Numbersight: A Street-Fighting Mathematician Teaches How to Make Better Decisions</i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prometheus_Books\">Prometheus Publishing</a></li>\n<li> <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>2014</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://mitpress.mit.edu/books/art-insight-science-and-engineering\">The Art of Insight in Science and Engineering</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIT_Press\">MIT Press</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sanjoy_Mahajan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.olin.edu/faculty/profile/sanjoy-mahajan/\">Faculty Profile for Sanjoy Mahajan, Ph.D. | Olin College</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.inference.phy.cam.ac.uk/sanjoy/\">Sanjoy Mahajan's Home Page</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://streetfightingmath.com/author.html\">Sanjoy Mahajan @ Street-Fighting Mathematics</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://web.mit.edu/sanjoy/www/\">Sanjoy Mahajan @ MIT</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sanjoy_Mahajan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://streetfightingmath.com/author.html\">Sanjoy Mahajan @ Street-Fighting Mathematics</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahajan\">Mahajan from Wikipedia</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://web.mit.edu/sanjoy/www/cv.pdf\">Sanjoy Mahajan CV</a> (pdf)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>1998</b>). <i>Order of Magnitude Physics - A Textbook with Applications to the Retinal Rod and to the Density of Prime Numbers</i>. Ph.D. thesis, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/California_Institute_of_Technology\">California Institute of Technology</a>, advisors <a href=\"/Mathematician#SPhinney\" title=\"Mathematician\">Sterl Phinney</a>, <a href=\"/Mathematician#JHopfield\" title=\"Mathematician\">John Hopfield</a> and <a href=\"/Mathematician#CAMead\" title=\"Mathematician\">Carver Mead</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.inference.phy.cam.ac.uk/sanjoy/thesis/thesis-letter.pdf\">pdf</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>2010</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://mitpress.mit.edu/books/street-fighting-mathematics\">Street-Fighting Mathematics: The Art of Educated Guessing and Opportunistic Problem Solving</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIT_Press\">MIT Press</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>2014</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://mitpress.mit.edu/books/art-insight-science-and-engineering\">The Art of Insight in Science and Engineering</a></i>. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIT_Press\">MIT Press</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/Kai-Fu_Lee\" title=\"Kai-Fu Lee\">Kai-Fu Lee</a>, <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Sanjoy Mahajan</a> (<b>1986</b>). <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://kilthub.cmu.edu/articles/BILL_a_table-based_knowledge-intensive_othello_program/6603887/1\">BILL: a table-based, knowledge-intensive othello program</a></i>. Technial Report CMU-CS-86-141, <a href=\"/Carnegie_Mellon_University\" title=\"Carnegie Mellon University\">Carnegie Mellon University</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.inference.phy.cam.ac.uk/sanjoy/othello/bill-1.0.tar.gz\">BILL: An Othello program released under the GPL</a> from <a rel=\"nofollow\" 